<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,437,1108]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,313,1002,1028]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
The distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[558,673,1002,1027]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lividus">
<emphasis box="[558,673,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">C. lividus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the 
<collectingRegion box="[911,965,1002,1028]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gulf</collectingRegion>
of Mannar. The occurrence of a larger number of specimens from Keelakarai may be associated with the fact that they generally inhabit the edges of the fringing reefs of the nearby coral islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
